  • Method Details

    • parseFormula

      public Map<Element,Integer> parseFormula(String formula) throws IOException
      A method for parsing a molecular formula into an occurrence mapping of the constituent elements to their frequencies. You can group element with parenthesis and apply counts to the groups (e.g. C2(HO)2). Any other symbols are stripped from the formula (e.g. - or +). Leaving them in does no harm
      Parameters:
      formula - The molecular formula of the compound as a String
      Returns:
      A mapping of Elements to their frequencies in the Compound
      Throws:
      IOException

    • getAmounts

      public HashMap<String,Float> getAmounts(String arg, float quantity)

      Parameters:

      quantity - The gram, mole, OR molecule amounts of the Compound
